<br>
If the group is in a high risk situation, a good healer will know to sit down and stick to healing only.  But if it's a low risk situation, having to heal only every two or three minutes can be incredibly boring, even to the most dedicated healer.  And honestly, if your healer is doing sit and heal service in an easy exp group, they're probably chatting it up in tells and /gu to pass the time anyways.  Therefore, that's mana and manpower going to waste.  <br>
<br>
Healing classes who melee in groups are also working on their skills.  Defense and offense can only be worked up while battling non-greenies.  And we suck at soloing.  So, it's a safe arena to do it.  Otherwise, my blunt and offensive skills wouldn't be maxxed and my defense wouldn't be nearly as high as it is (which means I can take more bruises when the MOBs turn on me).    <br>
<br>
If you're in a high-risk group with a Battle Priest and their meleeing makes you uncomfortable, talk with them nicely about it.  If they're compromising the group's health, they'll notice it and back off.  And if they don't, they're in the wrong profession and need to seriously consider taking up a sword.  Paladins are cool too.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://people.txucom.net/eldred/libsticksig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=635727" target="top"> Libbie's Stuff</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wyrdup>Wyrd Up</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1015<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/27/03 11:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3914.topic&index=30>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   *grin*</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>That is ALL for meleeing I have seen Shaman beat Warriors, SKs, Pallies and Monks of the same level in duals using Melee<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
